                    Program Advantages and Benefits
   [clearpixel.gif] [clearpixel.gif]

   Advancements in information technology can enhance any Federal agency's
   ability to operate more efficiently. Effective planning and
   implementation become increasingly more difficult as the technology
   becomes more complex. To assist the Federal community in fulfilling its
   Information Technology needs, GSA, Federal Information Systems Support
   Program (FISSP) offers a full spectrum of contracts and in-house
   services to meet this changing technological environment. Benefits
   include:
   [clearpixel.gif] [clearpixel.gif]

                    Broad Scope of Work
   [clearpixel.gif] [clearpixel.gif]

   FISSP contracts provide a full spectrum of support services spanning
   the complete life cycle of Information Technology needs.
   [clearpixel.gif] [clearpixel.gif]

                    Economies of Scale
   [clearpixel.gif] [clearpixel.gif]

   GSA achieves economies of scale through volume purchases and
   competitive procurement methods to award requirements contracts for use
   by Federal agencies.
   [clearpixel.gif] [clearpixel.gif]

                    Competitively Awarded Contracts
   [clearpixel.gif] [clearpixel.gif]

   The FISSP competitively awarded contracts meet both OMB Circular A-76
   and Federal Acquisition Regulation (FAR) requirements.
   [clearpixel.gif] [clearpixel.gif]

                    Project Management
   [clearpixel.gif] [clearpixel.gif]

   GSA provides dedicated, highly skilled technical and support
   representatives to administer the work and assist in the review and
   acceptance of deliverables and services.
   [clearpixel.gif] [clearpixel.gif]

                    Fast Start-up
   [clearpixel.gif] [clearpixel.gif]

   In-place contracts assure a 5-6 week average timeframe for work to
   begin on your task order.
   [clearpixel.gif] [clearpixel.gif]

                    Flexibility
   [clearpixel.gif] [clearpixel.gif]

   Work can be performed at the agency or contractor's site. Tasks can be
   based on a level of effort or fixed price. Funds obligated for FISSP
   task orders remains available for the life of the project.
   [clearpixel.gif] [clearpixel.gif]

                    Commitment to Quality
   [clearpixel.gif] [clearpixel.gif]

   FISSP personnel closely monitor contractor performance to ensure work
   quality and client satisfaction.
   [clearpixel.gif] [clearpixel.gif]

                    Empowerment
   [clearpixel.gif] [clearpixel.gif]

   Empowers you, the client agency, to react quickly to changing
   workloads. Enables you to easily take on new projects without
   increasing permanent staff or retraining current employees. Allows you
   to focus your in-house talents on your highest priorities. Reduces the
   number of contracts your agency has to manage.

   [clearpixel.gif]
